Historisch-genetische, theoretische und systematische, empirische und angewandte Aspekte ergänzen einander.  aThis work covers the full breadth of research on the rhetorical processes of social action for the purpose of communication. Unlike purely oratorical models of rhetoric, conversational rhetoric includes all modalities of mutual impact and problem solving in socio-communicative processes that employ linguistic signs. A focus is placed on the forms, structures, and functions of conversations in their various contexts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aConversation analysis. 0aRhetoricvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 4aDialoglinguistik. 4aDiskursforschung. 4aGesprächsanalyse. 4aGesprächsrhetorik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Rhetoric.2bisacsh  aConversation Analysis.  aConversational Rhetoric.  aDialogue Linguistics.  aDiscourse Research.1 aBendel Larcher, Sylvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergmann, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoothe, Brigitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBose, Ines, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBücker, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrescher, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEggs, Ekkehard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerwinski, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGronke, Horst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGruber, Helmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGutenberg, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHannken-Illjes, 